The paper deals with the study of locally decodable codes (LDCs), which are used in information theory and coding theory. The paper also involves Boolean functions, finite field incidence geometry, additive combinatorics, and hypergraph (non)expanders, which are all related to computer science. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
